ğŸš€ Getting Started

1. Install
git clone https://github.com/<your-repo>/caching-proxy.git
cd caching-proxy
npm install

2. Run the Proxy Server
caching-proxy --port 3000 --origin http://localhost:4000


3. Clear Cache
caching-proxy --clear-cache


âš™ï¸ How It Works

ìš”ì²­ íë¦„
Client â†’ Caching Proxy â†’ (cache MISS) â†’ Origin Server
                         â†‘
                       (cache HIT)

Cache Lookup Example
const cached = getCached(cacheKey);
if (cached) {
  res.setHeader("X-Cache", "HIT");
  return res.end(cached);
}

Origin Fetch â†’ Cache Store
http.get(proxyUrl, (originRes) => {
  let data = "";
  originRes.on("data", chunk => data += chunk);
  originRes.on("end", () => {
    setCached(cacheKey, data);
    res.setHeader("X-Cache", "MISS");
    res.end(data);
  });
});


